{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":12157,"name":"","username":"Victor","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/v/3e96dc/{size}.png","created_at":"2016-05-19T21:48:02.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI was wondering if there was a good way to draw text along a curve with the Text3D component? It seems like it would be ideal to use the text_ (and using the uiVertexData positions), private member variable to achieve this however there‚Äôs currently no possible way to access that variable outside of the class. Perhaps there‚Äôs another way? Using Text3D::GetRawData() just returns null so I‚Äôm not sure of another alternative to accomplish this. Thanks!\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:12:26.680Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":147,"reads":32,"readers_count":31,"score":741.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":2034,"topic_slug":"curved-text","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://discourse.urho3d.io/t/anti-aliased-lines-and-outlined-text-on-map-app/6106/6","internal":true,"reflection":true,"title":"Anti-Aliased Lines and Outlined Text on Map App","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":461,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":12160,"name":"Lasse √ñ√∂rni","username":"cadaver","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/cadaver/{size}/3_2.png","created_at":"2016-05-20T07:35:02.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eWill be a minor change to change text_ to protected and then you could subclass Text3D.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eEDIT: all Text3D data that was previously private is now protected in the master branch.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:12:26.851Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":32,"readers_count":31,"score":6.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":2034,"topic_slug":"curved-text","display_username":"Lasse √ñ√∂rni","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"Urho3D Author","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":true,"staff":true,"user_id":3,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":12163,"name":"","username":"Victor","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/v/3e96dc/{size}.png","created_at":"2016-05-20T13:51:38.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003e[quote=‚Äúcadaver‚Äù]Will be a minor change to change text_ to protected and then you could subclass Text3D.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eEDIT: all Text3D data that was previously private is now protected in the master branch.[/quote]\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAwesome thanks! I was just about to say that the uiBatches and uiVertexData were also things I would need but it seems you‚Äôve already taken care of that! \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/slight_smile.png?v=9\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slight_smile:\"\u003e Here‚Äôs what I got so far, although I‚Äôm still tweaking the curve. Thanks again man!\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"http://i.imgur.com/uWeoMpm.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"245\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:12:27.063Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":32,"readers_count":31,"score":11.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":2034,"topic_slug":"curved-text","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":461,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":12165,"name":"","username":"yushli","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/y/d6d6ee/{size}.png","created_at":"2016-05-20T16:03:39.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eThat looks like a nice feature to have. Care to share some code on how to achieve this?\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:12:27.222Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":30,"readers_count":29,"score":11.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":2034,"topic_slug":"curved-text","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":146,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":12166,"name":"","username":"Victor","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/v/3e96dc/{size}.png","created_at":"2016-05-20T16:12:57.000Z","cooked":"\u003caside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"yushli\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"title\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"quote-controls\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cimg alt=\"\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" src=\"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/y/d6d6ee/40.png\" class=\"avatar\"\u003e yushli:\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThat looks like a nice feature to have. Care to share some code on how to achieve this?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSure thing! Later tonight I‚Äôll create a repo and post what I have so far, but it‚Äôs not perfect. Maybe someone out there can perfect it though!\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eOne note however, I have noticed that values I get from Unity and Urho using the Vector math methods are different. To resolve this I‚Äôve been using the glm library for all vector/quaternion math. An example is when you have the following:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003eVector3 dir = (0, 0, 0);\nVector3 up = Vector3::UP;\nfloat angle Angle(dir, up)\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eYou‚Äôll either get back 0 or nan (can‚Äôt remember) for the angle. However Unity will translate this as 90.0 degrees. GLM returns back in radians, however once you convert it you would see that it returns 90 degrees as well. Not sure if I did something wrong but I just ended up using glm to be the happy medium in my port from Unity to Urho. Perhaps Urho was also returning radians and I just didn‚Äôt notice heh \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/slight_smile.png?v=10\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slight_smile:\"\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eEDIT:\u003cbr\u003e\nIf you see here \u003ca href=\"https://github.com/urho3d/Urho3D/blob/master/Source/Urho3D/Math/Vector3.h#L232\" data-bbcode=\"true\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"\u003ehttps://github.com/urho3d/Urho3D/blob/master/Source/Urho3D/Math/Vector3.h#L232\u003c/a\u003e it will find the magnitude of the dir and so you end up with a n / 0 case.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:12:27.301Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":29,"readers_count":28,"score":15.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":2034,"topic_slug":"curved-text","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://github.com/urho3d/Urho3D/blob/master/Source/Urho3D/Math/Vector3.h#L232","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Urho3D/Vector3.h at master ¬∑ urho3d/Urho3D ¬∑ GitHub","clicks":2}],"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":461,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":12177,"name":"","username":"Victor","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/v/3e96dc/{size}.png","created_at":"2016-05-21T05:10:50.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eStill working out some issues, so I probably won‚Äôt have any examples soon. However \u003cspan class=\"bbcode-b\"\u003eyushli\u003c/span\u003e, the only thing I‚Äôm really doing to curve my text is manipulating this example here:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://github.com/urho3d/Urho3D/blob/master/Source/Urho3D/UI/Text3D.cpp#L492-L542\" data-bbcode=\"true\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003ehttps://github.com/urho3d/Urho3D/blob/master/Source/Urho3D/UI/Text3D.cpp#L492-L542\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eYou can get a curve through using a parabola method like the following:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003e    static glm::vec3 SampleParabola(glm::vec3 start, glm::vec3 end, float height, float t)\n    {\n        if (glm::abs(start.y - end.y) \u0026lt; 0.1f)\n        {\n            //start and end are roughly level, pretend they are - simpler solution with less steps\n            glm::vec3 travelDirection = end - start;\n            glm::vec3 result = start + t * travelDirection;\n            result.y += glm::sin(t * glm::pi\u0026lt;float\u0026gt;()) * height;\n            return result;\n        }\n        else\n        {\n            //start and end are not level, gets more complicated\n            glm::vec3 travelDirection = end - start;\n            glm::vec3 levelDirection = end - glm::vec3(start.x, end.y, start.z);\n            glm::vec3 right = glm::cross(travelDirection, levelDirection);\n            glm::vec3 up = glm::cross(right, travelDirection);\n            if (end.y \u0026gt; start.y) up = -up;\n            glm::vec3 result = start + t * travelDirection;\n            result += (glm::sin(t * glm::pi\u0026lt;float\u0026gt;()) * height) * glm::normalize(up);\n            return result;\n        }\n    }\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI hope that helps!\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:12:28.117Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":26,"readers_count":25,"score":15.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":2034,"topic_slug":"curved-text","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://github.com/urho3d/Urho3D/blob/master/Source/Urho3D/UI/Text3D.cpp#L492-L542","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Urho3D/Text3D.cpp at master ¬∑ urho3d/Urho3D ¬∑ GitHub","clicks":7}],"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":461,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":12181,"name":"","username":"yushli","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/y/d6d6ee/{size}.png","created_at":"2016-05-21T14:16:10.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eThanks for your example code Victor. I will try it out. Take your time. Urho3d‚Äôs community is such a nice one as I can always get something new to learn from.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":7,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:12:28.404Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":21,"readers_count":20,"score":9.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":2034,"topic_slug":"curved-text","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":146,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":12183,"name":"","username":"Victor","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/v/3e96dc/{size}.png","created_at":"2016-05-21T16:10:10.000Z","cooked":"\u003caside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"yushli\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"title\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"quote-controls\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cimg alt=\"\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" src=\"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/y/d6d6ee/40.png\" class=\"avatar\"\u003e yushli:\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThanks for your example code Victor. I will try it out. Take your time. Urho3d‚Äôs community is such a nice one as I can always get something new to learn from.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eNo prob! When iterating over the vertexData you can handle each triangle in the following way as well:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003efor (unsigned i = 0; i \u0026lt; uiVertexData-\u0026gt;Size(); i += (UI_VERTEX_SIZE * 6)) {        \n        // Triangle #1\n        Vector3\u0026amp; v1 = *(reinterpret_cast\u0026lt;Vector3*\u0026gt;(\u0026amp;(*uiVertexData)[i]));  // Bottom-left\n        Vector3\u0026amp; v2 = *(reinterpret_cast\u0026lt;Vector3*\u0026gt;(\u0026amp;(*uiVertexData)[i + (UI_VERTEX_SIZE * 1)]));  // Bottom-right\n        Vector3\u0026amp; v3 = *(reinterpret_cast\u0026lt;Vector3*\u0026gt;(\u0026amp;(*uiVertexData)[i + (UI_VERTEX_SIZE * 2)]));  // Top-left\n\n        // Triangle #2\n        Vector3\u0026amp; v4 = *(reinterpret_cast\u0026lt;Vector3*\u0026gt;(\u0026amp;(*uiVertexData)[i + (UI_VERTEX_SIZE * 3)]));  // Bottom-right\n        Vector3\u0026amp; v5 = *(reinterpret_cast\u0026lt;Vector3*\u0026gt;(\u0026amp;(*uiVertexData)[i + (UI_VERTEX_SIZE * 4)]));  // Top-right\n        Vector3\u0026amp; v6 = *(reinterpret_cast\u0026lt;Vector3*\u0026gt;(\u0026amp;(*uiVertexData)[i + (UI_VERTEX_SIZE * 5)]));  // Top-left\n}\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBoth of those triangles will make up a single character. \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/slight_smile.png?v=10\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slight_smile:\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":8,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:12:28.525Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":21,"readers_count":20,"score":4.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":2034,"topic_slug":"curved-text","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":461,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":12235,"name":"","username":"Victor","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/v/3e96dc/{size}.png","created_at":"2016-05-26T08:04:58.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eSo I‚Äôm still working on solving this issue. I think the main issue I‚Äôm noticing is that when dealing with the vertices for a text object, I‚Äôm not able to convert world space coordinates properly for the text (I think this is my own fault for not understanding something properly). When attempting to apply the height of the text onto the terrain I start getting even weirder results. I also included a stroke effect to see what happens.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eMy goal is to convert my old project over into Urho. So far so good, just getting hung up on this text stuff. Perhaps this is more custom and I should try to rewrite a few things to fit my needs, but the world space to local space for the text object is really what seems to be my issue. Also, a way to set the min/max font size seems to be another hurdle I‚Äôm having as well.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eMy Urho Example (sorry, I haven‚Äôt implemented water yet, that‚Äôs next!):\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cimg src=\"http://i.imgur.com/oVtqiVh.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eMy Old Example:\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cimg src=\"http://i.imgur.com/9rcfwu0.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"448\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eOne huge plus about Urho so far is the fact that it‚Äôs super fast when loading all of these textures/data points!\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":9,"post_type":1,"